<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="273" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2757</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCAdR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1317</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="center">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>His Britannic Majesty’s Chargé d’Affaires presents his compliments to the
                            Secretary of State and, with reference to the memorandum from His
                            Majesty’s Embassy No. 1305 of November 20th, has the honour to inform
                            him by direction of His Majesty’s Government that <persName>King
                                Hussein</persName> has asked His Majesty’s Commissioner at Cairo to
                            convey to His Majesty’s Government the formal ratification of the fact
                            that his son, Emir Feisal, is proceeding as his representative to Paris.
                            The <persName>King</persName> has also asked that a similar notification
                            may be made by the British Government in his name to the United States,
                            French, and Italian Governments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-22">November
                                    22, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>